node.text:
Topping Tulips via @mikevdwesteringh 🌷🤩 These endless flowers fields are currently a dream itself. When in the Netherlands, you have to visit one of their breathtaking tulip fields. 🌷

Tulip season spans from the end of March until mid May, but the flowers are usually at their finest halfway through April. Witnessing millions of tulips blooming is a dream come true, especially with that colorful varieties from red, pink, white, yellow, and purple. 😍

Travel tip: When in Netherlands pay a visit to Keukenhof, also known as the Garden of Europe, is one of the world's largest flower gardens, situated in the municipality of Lisse, in the Netherlands. According to the official website, Keukenhof Park covers an area of 32 hectares and approximately 7 million flower bulbs are planted in the gardens annually.

📽 @mikevdwesteringh
📍Zeewolde, Netherlands
🎶 Beautiful Mate - Moonman

Rainbow Island, Iran 🇮🇷 The soil composing Hormuz Island in #Iran is highly concentrated with Iron Oxide. This concentration leads to red coloration, which is washed up in the waves.
Have you ever seen anything like this?

📽 @elhamgholami
